CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1953, pg. 31 reads: "At IKS May Festival - When Irene Kaufmann opened its playground on May 1 with its annual pageant and parade for children, called the "May Festival." Mrs. Anne Rose, afternoon program supervisor, crowned these four children as winners of some of the may events.  Left to right: Mrs. Rose, Delilah Moten, George Ransan, Casandra Williams and John Brown. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of two winners of May Festival pageant, Casandra Williams and George Ransan, at Irene Kaufmann Settlement
